&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded in 2017, Wayve is the leading developer of Embodied AI technology.&amp;nbsp; Our advanced AI software and foundation models enable vehicles to perceive, understand, and navigate any complex environment, enhancing the usability and safety of automated driving systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to create autonomy that propels the world forward.&amp;nbsp; Our intelligent, mapless, and hardware-agnostic AI products are designed for automakers, accelerating the transition from assisted to automated driving.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In our fast-paced environment big problems ignite us—we embrace uncertainty, leaning into complex challenges to unlock groundbreaking solutions. We aim high and stay humble in our pursuit of excellence, constantly learning and evolving as we pave the way for a smarter, safer future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Wayve, your contributions matter.&amp;nbsp; We value diversity, embrace new perspectives, and foster an inclusive work environment; we back each other to deliver impact.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Make Wayve the experience that defines your career!&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced Hardware Engineer to join our Hardware team and play a key role in developing next-generation autonomous driving compute platforms. This role focuses on low-level electronics design, embedded systems, and high-performance compute integration translating autonomy requirements into robust, scalable hardware systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work hands-on with cutting-edge computing platforms, collaborating across hardware, software, and systems teams to design, bring up, and validate mission-critical electronics that enable embodied AI.&lt;/p&gt;
